{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbf4e3da1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11431"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11431"},"text":"§ 11431.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Statement of policy","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The following is the policy of the Congress:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf4e3da2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11431/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Each State educational agency shall ensure that each child of a homeless individual and each homeless youth has equal access to the same free, appropriate public education, including a public preschool education, as provided to other children and youths.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf4e3da3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11431/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" In any State where compulsory residency requirements or other requirements, in laws, regulations, practices, or policies, may act as a barrier to the identification of, or the enrollment, attendance, or success in school of, homeless children and youths, the State educational agency and local educational agencies in the State will review and undertake steps to revise such laws, regulations, practices, or policies to ensure that homeless children and youths are afforded the same free, appropriate public education as provided to other children and youths.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf4e3da4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11431/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Homelessness is not sufficient reason to separate students from the mainstream school environment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbf4e3da5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s11431/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Homeless children and youths should have access to the education and other services that such children and youths need to ensure that such children and youths have an opportunity to meet the same challenging State academic standards to which all students are held.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbf4e3da6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/77/tVII/s721"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–77, title VII, § 721","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/110/tX/s1032"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–110, title X, § 1032","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-01-08"},"text":"Jan. 8, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/1989"},"text":"115 Stat. 1989","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/95/tIX/s9101"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–95, title IX, § 9101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/2124"},"text":"129 Stat. 2124","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbf4e3da7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbf4e3da8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idbf4e3da9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 11431, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/77/tVII/s721"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–77, title VII, § 721","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/382/tIII/s323"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–382, title III, § 323","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-20"},"text":"Oct. 20, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3957"},"text":"108 Stat. 3957","children":[],"tail":", stated policy of Congress, prior to the general amendment of this part by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/110"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–110","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Another prior section 11431, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/77/tVII/s721"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–77, title VII, § 721","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-07-22"},"text":"July 22, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/525"},"text":"101 Stat. 525","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/645/tVI/s612/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–645, title VI, § 612(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/4735"},"text":"104 Stat. 4735","children":[],"tail":", stated policy of Congress, prior to the general amendment of this part by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/382"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–382","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbf4e3daa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/95/s9101/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–95, § 9101(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “In any State where compulsory residency requirements or other requirements, in laws, regulations, practices, or policies, may act as a barrier to the identification of, or the enrollment, attendance, or success in school of, homeless children and youths, the State educational agency and local educational agencies in the State will review” for “In any State that has a compulsory residency requirement as a component of the State’s compulsory school attendance laws or other laws, regulations, practices, or policies that may act as a barrier to the enrollment, attendance, or success in school of homeless children and youths, the State will review”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/95/s9101/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–95, § 9101(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “alone” after “Homelessness”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/95/s9101/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–95, § 9101(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “challenging State academic standards” for “challenging State student academic achievement standards”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbf4e3dab-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbf4e3dac-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2015 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/95/tIX/s9107"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–95, title IX, § 9107","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/2137"},"text":"129 Stat. 2137","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/114/95/tIX/s9107"},"text":"“Except as provided in section 9105(b) [set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11434a"},"text":"section 11434a of this title","children":[],"tail":"] or as otherwise provided in this Act [see Tables for classification], this title [probably means “this part”, meaning part A (§§ 9101–9107) of title IX of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/95"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–95","children":[],"tail":", amending this section and sections 11432 to 11435 of this title and enacting provisions set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s11434a"},"text":"section 11434a of this title","children":[],"tail":"] and the amendments made by this title take effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 2016","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idbf4e3dad-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-01-08"},"text":"Jan. 8, 2002","children":[],"tail":", except with respect to certain noncompetitive programs and competitive programs, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/110/s5"},"text":"section 5 of Pub. L. 107–110","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"